              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">Week 3: User flow issues‚Äîvisitors confused about next steps, trial signups dropping.</p>

              <div class="bg-teal-100 border-l-[4px] border-teal-500 p-4 my-4">
                <p class="text-sm text-teal-900 font-medium"><strong>The rebuild:</strong> Spent 6 weeks restructuring, adding pages, fixing flow. Missed investor meeting deadline. Lost a $250,000 investment opportunity. The founders were furious. I felt terrible.</p>
              </div>

              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed"><strong>The right route: Relume + Framer (learned the hard way)</strong></p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">Six months later, another SaaS startup. Different approach.</p>

              <div class="bg-cyan-100 border-l-[4px] border-cyan-500 p-4 my-4">
                <p class="text-sm text-cyan-900 font-medium"><strong>The Relume workflow:</strong> Spent 90 minutes planning the complete sitemap. Generated 32-page wireframe with Relume. Found 3 missing pages in planning phase. Restructured user flow based on stakeholder feedback. All before writing a single line of design code.</p>
              </div>

              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">Exported wireframes to Framer. Built the actual site with custom design in 3 weeks. Hit investor deadline. Investors were impressed. Secured $500,000 in funding.</p>

              <div class="bg-emerald-100 border-l-[4px] border-emerald-500 p-4 my-4">
                <p class="text-sm text-emerald-900 font-medium"><strong>The lesson:</strong> Planning isn't optional‚Äîit's the most important phase. Relume costs $0-20/month. Lost funding opportunities cost $250,000+. The ROI on proper planning is infinite.</p>
              </div>

              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed"><strong>But when IS Durable the right choice?</strong></p>
